content:
Using a cache to store frequently accessed, infrequently updated data saves round trips to the database and improves performance.

A Cache Block saves the output of steps within it to a session or org cache in the VlocityAPIResponse cache partition for quick retrieval. This can be useful if some parts of an Integration Procedure update data, or if different cached data should expire at different times.

When testing a Cache Block in Preview mode, you can use two caching settings: ignoreCache and resetCache. Setting ignoreCache to false allows you to test caching, while setting resetCache to true forces data to be saved to the cache.

The following JSON nodes may appear in the Debug Log output of an active Integration Procedure that uses a Cache Block:

* vlcCacheKey - Key for any data stored in the cache
* vlcCacheResult - Included and set to true if data is retrieved from the cache
* vlcCacheEnabled - Included and set to false if caching is disabled
* vlcCacheException - Any caching errors

Apex methods are available to clear Cache Block data from the cache, including clearing all cached data for an Integration Procedure. 

Use Cache Blocks if some parts of an Integration Procedure update data and therefore shouldn't be cached, or if different cached data should expire at different times.

To create a Cache Block example, you can improve Contact retrieval performance by accepting a list of first or last names and retrieving Contacts having those names.
title: Enhancing Performance with OmniStudio Cache Blocks
